{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Hpq5DMEdphKX3s5TbhU2LW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me refactor all the Java source files. The key changes needed for Quarkus:\n\n1. `@PersistenceContext` -> `@Inject` for EntityManager\n2. `@Dependent` / `@Singleton` -> `@ApplicationScoped` for DAOs\n3. `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces` -> needs to coexist with Quarkus (no change needed for CDI annotations - jakarta.inject and jakarta.enterprise are still used in Quarkus)\n4. Remove Liberty-specific configs\n5. The `@Secured` annotation + filters use JAX-RS `@NameBinding` which works in Quarkus RESTEasy\n\nThe good news is that Quarkus fully supports Jakarta CDI, JAX-RS, JPA, and Validation annotations. Most of the code can stay as-is. The main changes needed are:\n\n1. AbstractDAO: `@PersistenceContext` -> `@Inject` \n2. SerializerConfig: CDI `@Produces` conflict with Quarkus - needs different approach\n3. Remove persistence.xml (use application.properties instead) or update it\n4. Remove Liberty server.xml\n5. Remove beans.xml (Quarkus doesn't need it)\n6. Remove microprofile-config.properties (use application.properties)\n\nLet me do all the code modifications:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":431,"cache_read_input_tokens":116287,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":431,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":525},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"3df610ad-b6eb-4a78-a6f8-484f5a352131"}
