{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FApzfPN9KpUoRpbuNo8yWa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     7→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     8→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     9→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n    10→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.*;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n    16→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewArticleRequestWrapper;\n    17→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewCommentRequestWrapper;\n    18→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.UpdateArticleRequestWrapper;\n    19→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils.ResourceUtils;\n    20→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n    21→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleFilter;\n    22→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.DeleteCommentInput;\n    23→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    24→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;\n    25→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.annotation.Secured;\n    26→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.profile.Role;\n    27→\n    28→import java.util.List;\n    29→import java.util.UUID;\n    30→\n    31→@Path(\"/articles\")\n    32→public class ArticlesResource {\n    33→\n    34→    @Inject\n    35→    private FindArticlesByFilter findArticlesByFilter;\n    36→    @Inject\n    37→    private CreateArticle createArticle;\n    38→    @Inject\n    39→    private FindMostRecentArticlesByFilter findMostRecentArticlesByFilter;\n    40→    @Inject\n    41→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    42→    @Inject\n    43→    private UpdateArticleBySlug updateArticleBySlug;\n    44→    @Inject\n    45→    private DeleteArticleBySlug deleteArticleBySlug;\n    46→    @Inject\n    47→    private CreateComment createComment;\n    48→    @Inject\n    49→    private DeleteComment deleteComment;\n    50→    @Inject\n    51→    private FindCommentsByArticleSlug findCommentsByArticleSlug;\n    52→    @Inject\n    53→    private FavoriteArticle favoriteArticle;\n    54→    @Inject\n    55→    private UnfavoriteArticle unfavoriteArticle;\n    56→    @Inject\n    57→    private ResourceUtils resourceUtils;\n    58→    @Inject\n    59→    @Named(\"wrapRootValue\")\n    60→    ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    61→    @Inject\n    62→    @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper\n    63→    ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper;\n    64→\n    65→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014vAcH28SUJsZvaxSH8c7QL","session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"00b9919a-da9a-43fd-89f5-11dd396aeeff"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014W12MfBnAiaoDh2Ywe9uP5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.ExceptionMapper;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.ErrorResponse;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.*;\n    12→\n    13→import java.util.HashMap;\n    14→import java.util.Map;\n    15→import java.util.function.Function;\n    16→\n    17→@Provider\n    18→public class BusinessExceptionMapper implements ExceptionMapper<BusinessException> {\n    19→\n    20→    @Inject\n    21→    @Named(\"wrapRootValue\")\n    22→    ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    23→\n    24→    private final Map<Class<? extends BusinessException>, Function<BusinessException, Response>>\n    25→            exceptionMapper;\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014vAcH28SUJsZvaxSH8c7QL","session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"f15d03a8-c691-4e54-bea7-5011752f8518"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014vAcH28SUJsZvaxSH8c7QL","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! All updates have been successfully completed. Let me provide a summary of all the changes made:\n\n## Summary\n\nI have successfully updated all 7 Java files in the project to add the `@Named(\"wrapRootValue\")` qualifier to unqualified ObjectMapper injections. Here are the details of the changes:\n\n### Files Updated:\n\n1. **ArticlesResource.java** (`/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java`)\n   - Added `import jakarta.inject.Named;`\n   - Added `@Named(\"wrapRootValue\")` to the unqualified `ObjectMapper objectMapper` (line 58-60)\n   - Left `@NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper` unchanged (line 61-63)\n\n2. **UserResource.java** (`/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java`)\n   - Added `import jakarta.inject.Named;`\n   - Added `@Named(\"wrapRootValue\")` to `private ObjectMapper objectMapper`\n\n3. **UsersResource.java** (`/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java`)\n   - Added `import jakarta.inject.Named;`\n   - Added `@Named(\"wrapRootValue\")` to `private ObjectMapper objectMapper`\n\n4. **ProfilesResource.java** (`/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java`)\n   - Added `import jakarta.inject.