{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HUef8UmffQtwFxJipxDW5n","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n     6→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     8→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     9→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n    10→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n    11→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.*;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n    17→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewArticleRequestWrapper;\n    18→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.NewCommentRequestWrapper;\n    19→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.UpdateArticleRequestWrapper;\n    20→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils.ResourceUtils;\n    21→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n    22→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleFilter;\n    23→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.DeleteCommentInput;\n    24→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    25→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;\n    26→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.annotation.Secured;\n    27→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.profile.Role;\n    28→\n    29→import java.util.List;\n    30→import java.util.UUID;\n    31→\n    32→@RequestScoped\n    33→@Path(\"/articles\")\n    34→public class ArticlesResource {\n    35→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0119NREnhimgZbexnWCgTfa3","session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"80759812-b79c-4400-9460-2e4cb9f36a10"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0119NREnhimgZbexnWCgTfa3","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! All the changes have been successfully applied. Let me provide a summary of what was done:\n\n## Summary\n\nI have successfully added the `@RequestScoped` annotation to all five JAX-RS resource classes in the project. This annotation is required in Quarkus for field injection to work properly with CDI (Contexts and Dependency Injection).\n\n### Files Updated:\n\n1. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java**\n   - Added import: `jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped`\n   - Added `@RequestScoped` annotation before `@Path(\"/articles\")`\n\n2. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java**\n   - Added import: `jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped`\n   - Added `@RequestScoped` annotation before `@Path(\"/user\")`\n\n3. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java**\n   - Added import: `jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped`\n   - Added `@RequestScoped` annotation before `@Path(\"/users\")`\n\n4. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java**\n   - Added import: `jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped`\n   - Added `@RequestScoped` annotation before `@Path(\"/profiles\")`\n\n5. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/TagsResource.java**\n   - Added import: `jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped`\n   - Added `@RequestScoped` annotation before `@Path(\"/tags\")`\n\n### What This Fixes:\n\nThe `@RequestScoped` annotation provides an explicit CDI scope for these JAX-RS resources. In Quarkus, when you use `@Inject` for field injection (as these classes do), the bean needs to have a CDI scope annotation. Without it, CDI may not properly manage the bean lifecycle, leading to injection failures. The `@RequestScoped` annotation ensures that a new instance of the resource is created for each HTTP request, which is the appropriate scope for REST API endpoints."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"c50309bf-90c0-427a-a121-fbbd4b09d4e5"}
