{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_0199xuqeshL2GFsCi6L9gtWT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I can see the issue clearly! The problem is:\n\n> `Root name ('user') does not match expected ('NewUserRequestWrapper')`\n\nThe Quarkus default ObjectMapper has `UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` enabled (from the global Quarkus ObjectMapper customizer). The JSON body `{\"user\": {...}}` is treated as a root-wrapped value, and Jackson expects the root name to match the class name `NewUserRequestWrapper`, not `user`.\n\nThe fix: The `NewUserRequestWrapper` is a regular POJO with a `user` field - it doesn't use `@JsonRootName`. The default Quarkus ObjectMapper should NOT have `UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` enabled. The wrap/unwrap is only needed for the custom `@Named(\"wrapRootValue\")` ObjectMapper used explicitly in the resource methods for serializing responses.\n\nThe issue is that the default Quarkus ObjectMapper is somehow getting UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE. Let me create an `ObjectMapperCustomizer` to make sure the default Quarkus ObjectMapper works correctly:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1716,"cache_read_input_tokens":142405,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1716,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":370},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"8e65ddbe-80f4-4bc6-897c-bf39fe27841d"}
