{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01CqSMBxB9HoxpuBM8vX27Mk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE is still being applied to the Quarkus default ObjectMapper. The `ObjectMapperCustomizer` approach is correct, but the CDI `@Produces ObjectMapper` with `@Named(\"wrapRootValue\")` might still be getting picked up by Quarkus as the default ObjectMapper because Quarkus might select it over its own. \n\nWait - actually, the issue is that the `ObjectMapperCustomizer` produced via `@Produces` may not work the same way as a direct CDI bean. In Quarkus, the `ObjectMapperCustomizer` needs to be a CDI bean itself, not produced. Let me fix this differently - make it a standalone bean:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":460,"cache_read_input_tokens":147488,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":460,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":437},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"0674cec3-1c01-447b-bea4-d01b86c2a48a"}
