{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01HACcJD3L4bu4EVzvFSLvB7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The same UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE error is still happening. This means Quarkus's default ObjectMapper still has UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE enabled. The `@Named(\"wrapRootValue\")` CDI producer might still be getting picked up as an alternative for the default ObjectMapper.\n\nThe problem is that in Quarkus, when you produce an `ObjectMapper` bean (even with a qualifier), it might interfere with Quarkus's own ObjectMapper. The `@Named` qualifier is supposed to prevent this, but Quarkus RESTEasy Reactive Jackson might be picking it up.\n\nThe real fix is to not produce ObjectMapper beans at all via CDI `@Produces`, and instead just create them manually. Let me take a different approach - remove the CDI producers for ObjectMapper and just construct them in the places they're needed:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":537,"cache_read_input_tokens":128634,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":537,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":314},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"6b7b6984-2688-47e0-9777-0af2f74b69d9"}
