{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015CRK4S5TZra1W6q9qBbSts","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.config;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.DeserializationFeature;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.SerializationFeature;\n     6→import com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jsr310.JavaTimeModule;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    10→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;\n    12→\n    13→@ApplicationScoped\n    14→public class SerializerConfig {\n    15→\n    16→    /**\n    17→     * Custom ObjectMapper with WRAP_ROOT_VALUE enabled for manual serialization of responses.\n    18→     * This is NOT the default Quarkus ObjectMapper - it's injected via @Named(\"wrapRootValue\").\n    19→     */\n    20→    @Singleton\n    21→    @Produces\n    22→    @Named(\"wrapRootValue\")\n    23→    public ObjectMapper objectMapper() {\n    24→        ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n    25→        objectMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n    26→        objectMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n    27→        objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    28→        return objectMapper;\n    29→    }\n    30→\n    31→    @Singleton\n    32→    @Produces\n    33→    @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper\n    34→    public ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n    35→        return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→}\n    39→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"dde72aeb-e75a-4ced-a43d-f4f8215d4563"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01SzGdhgjmnbed8rr1Gx5Hk7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Actually, looking at the Quarkus documentation, the issue might be that `@Named` doesn't prevent Quarkus from using the produced ObjectMapper as the default. I need to ensure these ObjectMapper instances are never selected as the default. Let me use a different approach - use `@Alternative` or just make them completely separate:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":916,"cache_read_input_tokens":129171,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":916,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":589},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"b3b49874-dcbe-4fb7-aac0-5fc01d5d1f9e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01SzGdhgjmnbed8rr1Gx5Hk7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01GEsA9RdVDWFYPmCoCHmxkv","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/config/SerializerConfig.java","content":"package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.config;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.DeserializationFeature;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.SerializationFeature;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jsr310.JavaTimeModule;\nimport jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n\n/**\n * Provides pre-configured ObjectMapper instances for manual serialization.\n * These are NOT CDI producers to avoid interfering with Quarkus's default ObjectMapper.\n */\n@Singleton\npublic class SerializerConfig {\n\n    private final ObjectMapper wrapRootValueMapper;\n    private final ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueMapper;\n\n    public SerializerConfig() {\n        this.wrapRootValueMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n        this.wrapRootValueMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n        this.wrapRootValueMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n        this.wrapRootValueMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n\n        this.noWrapRootValueMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n        this.noWrapRootValueMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    }\n\n    public ObjectMapper getWrapRootValueMapper() {\n        return wrapRootValueMapper;\n    }\n\n    public ObjectMapper getNoWrapRootValueMapper() {\n        return noWrapRootValueMapper;\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":916,"cache_read_input_tokens":129171,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":916,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":589},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"d035b70f-c321-4b0a-8896-f2b7b8bc0fe2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GEsA9RdVDWFYPmCoCHmxkv","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/config/SerializerConfig.java has been updated. Here's the result of running `cat -n` on a snippet of the edited file:\n     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.config;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.DeserializationFeature;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.SerializationFeature;\n     6→import com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jsr310.JavaTimeModule;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * Provides pre-configured ObjectMapper instances for manual serialization.\n    11→ * These are NOT CDI producers to avoid interfering with Quarkus's default ObjectMapper.\n    12→ */\n    13→@Singleton\n    14→public class SerializerConfig {\n    15→\n    16→    private final ObjectMapper wrapRootValueMapper;\n    17→    private final ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueMapper;\n    18→\n    19→    public SerializerConfig() {\n    20→        this.wrapRootValueMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n    21→        this.wrapRootValueMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n    22→        this.wrapRootValueMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n    23→        this.wrapRootValueMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    24→\n    25→        this.noWrapRootValueMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n    26→        this.noWrapRootValueMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    27→    }\n    28→\n    29→    public ObjectMapper getWrapRootValueMapper() {\n    30→        return wrapRootValueMapper;\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    public ObjectMapper getNoWrapRootValueMapper() {\n    34→        return noWrapRootValueMapper;\n    35→    }\n    36→}\n    37→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"2041f069-ad9f-4c71-a2f1-d60f9fad9cc2"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01XRCYUM39uNhc1jZ5Ktz2be","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I need to update all the resource classes and exception mappers that used `@Inject @Named(\"wrapRootValue\") ObjectMapper` to instead inject `SerializerConfig` and get the mapper from it. Let me also update the ones that used `@NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper`:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1451,"cache_read_input_tokens":130087,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1451,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1424},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"e279b261-d579-41b0-9cbf-43c008e13f7b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01XRCYUM39uNhc1jZ5Ktz2be","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_013YajV6UPrrreWyBgWbEiB9","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Update ObjectMapper injection pattern","prompt":"I need to update multiple Java files in the project at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output to use a new ObjectMapper access pattern. Instead of injecting ObjectMapper directly, they should inject SerializerConfig and call getWrapRootValueMapper() or getNoWrapRootValueMapper().\n\nHere are the files to update:\n\n### Files that inject @Named(\"wrapRootValue\") ObjectMapper:\nThese all need to change from:\n```java\n@Inject\n@Named(\"wrapRootValue\")\nprivate ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n```\nOR:\n```java\n@Inject\n@Named(\"wrapRootValue\")\nObjectMapper objectMapper;\n```\nto:\n```java\n@Inject\nSerializerConfig serializerConfig;\n```\nAnd then everywhere that `objectMapper` is used, replace with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper()`.\n\nAlso add the import for `org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.config.SerializerConfig` and remove the import for `jakarta.inject.Named` (if no other @Named usage remains).\n\nFiles to update:\n1. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java\n   - Change the `@Named(\"wrapRootValue\")` ObjectMapper injection to use SerializerConfig\n   - It also has `@NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper` - change that too to use serializerConfig.getNoWrapRootValueMapper()\n   - Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n   - Replace all `noWrapObjectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getNoWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n   \n2. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java\n   - Change the ObjectMapper injection to use SerializerConfig\n   - Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n\n3. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java\n   - Change the ObjectMapper injection to use SerializerConfig\n   - Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n\n4. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java\n   - Change the ObjectMapper injection to use SerializerConfig\n   - Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n\n5. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/BusinessExceptionMapper.java\n   - Change the ObjectMapper injection to use SerializerConfig\n   - Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n\n6. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/BeanValidationExceptionMapper.java\n   - Change the ObjectMapper injection to use SerializerConfig\n   - Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n\n7. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/InfrastructureExceptionMapper.java\n   - Change the ObjectMapper injection to use SerializerConfig\n   - Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n\nFor each file:\n1. Read the file\n2. Remove the `@Inject @Named(\"wrapRootValue\") ObjectMapper objectMapper;` field\n3. Remove the `@Inject @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper;` field (if present)\n4. Add `@Inject SerializerConfig serializerConfig;` field (make it private if the old field was private)\n5. Add import for `org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.config.SerializerConfig`\n6. Remove import for `jakarta.inject.Named` if no other @Named usage\n7. Remove import for `com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper` if no other ObjectMapper usage remains (note: some files may still create ObjectMapper locally, so check before removing)\n8. Remove import for `org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper` if present\n9. Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(`\n10. Replace all `noWrapObjectMapper.writeValueAsString(` with `serializerConfig.getNoWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(`\n\nMake ALL these changes now. Be very thorough.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1451,"cache_read_input_tokens":130087,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1451,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1424},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"a54e6527-42be-46f2-85d7-6e7066bdbf28"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need to update multiple Java files in the project at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output to use a new ObjectMapper access pattern. Instead of injecting ObjectMapper directly, they should inject SerializerConfig and call getWrapRootValueMapper() or getNoWrapRootValueMapper().\n\nHere are the files to update:\n\n### Files that inject @Named(\"wrapRootValue\") ObjectMapper:\nThese all need to change from:\n```java\n@Inject\n@Named(\"wrapRootValue\")\nprivate ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n```\nOR:\n```java\n@Inject\n@Named(\"wrapRootValue\")\nObjectMapper objectMapper;\n```\nto:\n```java\n@Inject\nSerializerConfig serializerConfig;\n```\nAnd then everywhere that `objectMapper` is used, replace with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper()`.\n\nAlso add the import for `org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.config.SerializerConfig` and remove the import for `jakarta.inject.Named` (if no other @Named usage remains).\n\nFiles to update:\n1. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java\n   - Change the `@Named(\"wrapRootValue\")` ObjectMapper injection to use SerializerConfig\n   - It also has `@NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper` - change that too to use serializerConfig.getNoWrapRootValueMapper()\n   - Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n   - Replace all `noWrapObjectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getNoWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n   \n2. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java\n   - Change the ObjectMapper injection to use SerializerConfig\n   - Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n\n3. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java\n   - Change the ObjectMapper injection to use SerializerConfig\n   - Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n\n4. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java\n   - Change the ObjectMapper injection to use SerializerConfig\n   - Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n\n5. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/BusinessExceptionMapper.java\n   - Change the ObjectMapper injection to use SerializerConfig\n   - Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n\n6. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/BeanValidationExceptionMapper.java\n   - Change the ObjectMapper injection to use SerializerConfig\n   - Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n\n7. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/InfrastructureExceptionMapper.java\n   - Change the ObjectMapper injection to use SerializerConfig\n   - Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(...)` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(...)`\n\nFor each file:\n1. Read the file\n2. Remove the `@Inject @Named(\"wrapRootValue\") ObjectMapper objectMapper;` field\n3. Remove the `@Inject @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper ObjectMapper noWrapObjectMapper;` field (if present)\n4. Add `@Inject SerializerConfig serializerConfig;` field (make it private if the old field was private)\n5. Add import for `org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.config.SerializerConfig`\n6. Remove import for `jakarta.inject.Named` if no other @Named usage\n7. Remove import for `com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper` if no other ObjectMapper usage remains (note: some files may still create ObjectMapper locally, so check before removing)\n8. Remove import for `org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper` if present\n9. Replace all `objectMapper.writeValueAsString(` with `serializerConfig.getWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(`\n10. Replace all `noWrapObjectMapper.writeValueAsString(` with `serializerConfig.getNoWrapRootValueMapper().writeValueAsString(`\n\nMake ALL these changes now. Be very thorough."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013YajV6UPrrreWyBgWbEiB9","session_id":"2092f313-8131-46b3-b954-3b9c381a11ae","uuid":"8c4e1dd4-df52-4d8a-9e2a-8b22b0271436"}
